{{Infobox civilian attack | title = 2004 Lahsuna massacre | partof = | image = | image_size = | image_upright = | alt = | caption = | map = | map_size = | map_alt = | map_caption = | location = Lahsuna, [[Bihar]], [[India]] | coordinates = {{coord|25.423212|85.032034|display=inline, title}} | fatalities = 4 | convicted = 3 }}
On 18 May 2004, four people were massacred at Lahsuna village in [[Bihar]] state of India.<ref name=a>{{cite web |author=Published: Saturday, January 5, 2008, 17:02 [IST] |url=https://www.oneindia.com/2008/01/04/death-for-three-in-lahsuna-massacre-1199532754.html |title=Death for three in Lahsuna Massacre |publisher=Oneindia.com |date=2008-01-05 |accessdate=2018-06-12 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612074932/https://www.oneindia.com/2008/01/04/death-for-three-in-lahsuna-massacre-1199532754.html |archivedate=June 12, 2018 |df= }}</ref><ref name=b>{{cite web|url=http://www.patnadaily.com/news2008/jan/010408/death_penalties_for_ultras.html|title=Death Penalties for 3 Former PWG Ultras|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080704214741/https://www.patnadaily.com/news2008/jan/010408/death_penalties_for_ultras.html|archivedate=4 July 2008}}</ref>
Members of the [[People's War Group]], a outlawed [[naxal]] group, were accused of the crime. About 100 armed members of the group reportedly dragged the victims out of their homes and killed them for casting their votes in favour of [[Janata Dal (United)]].<ref name=b />
The victims were identified as Uday Paswan, Naga Paswan, Vijay Paswan and Sarwan Paswan.<ref name=a />
In 2008, three members of the group were found guilty of the killings and were awarded [[capital punishment]] by a court in Patna.<ref name=a />
