The '''Canelos-Quichua''', also known as the '''Quichua of Pastaza''', is an [[Indigenous people of Ecuador]]. They are a Lowland Quichua (Runa Shimi) people, inhabiting the province of [[Pastaza Province|Pastaza]] on the banks of the [[Curaray River|Curaray]], Bonbonaza, and [[Pastaza River|Pastaza rivers]], in [[Peru]] and [[Ecuador]].

